From cou.: 18 Statistical analysis of the results was based on a multinomial logistic regression model. For a categorized response, Y takes values in a range of m categories (denoted as 1, 2,…,m) and has an associated vector of k covariates (x1,…,xk). The probability that Y is in the category i, conditional to covariates, is expressed as:This last expression permits an easy interpretation of β(i)j coefficients, quantifying the change in the probability ratio relative to the reference category m associated with a change in covariate xj.
From Soup: 18 Statistical analysis of the results was based on a multinomial logistic regression model. For a categorized response, Y takes values in a range of m categories (denoted as 1, 2,…, m ) and has an associated vector of k covariates ( x 1 ,…, x k ). The probability that Y is in the category i , conditional to covariates, is expressed as: This last expression permits an easy interpretation of β ( i ) j coefficients, quantifying the change in the probability ratio relative to the reference category m associated with a change in covariate x j .
