From Soup: 26 In order to facilitate the interpretation of the results obtained in this article, we propose a chemotactic index (CI) as a phenomenological perspective. There exist a wide variety of definitions for this index in the literature, 42,54–56 however, in this work, the CI is simply defined as the difference between the estimated proportion of cells in a zone with GF and the opposite zone (where there is not any GF). Hence, we propose this definition: where i represents the channel with GF and j the opposite one.
